        p.text &OpenCurlyQuote;Morning&comma; Jeeves&comma;&rsquor; I said&period;
        p.text &OpenCurlyQuote;Good morning&comma; sir&comma;&rsquor; said Jeeves&period;
        p.text
          | He put the good old cup of tea softly on the table by my bed&comma; and I took a refreshing sip&period; Just right&comma; as usual&period; Not to hot&comma; not too sweet&comma; not too weak&comma; not too strong&comma; not too much milk&comma; and not a drop spilled in the saucer&period; A most amazing cove&comma; Jeeves&period; So dashed competent in every respect&period; I&rsquor;ve said it before&comma; and I&rsquor;ll say it again&period; I mean to say&comma; take just one small instance&period; Every other valet I&rsquor;ve ever had used to barge into my room in the morning while I was still asleep&comma; causing much misery&semi; but Jeeves seems to know when I&rsquor;m awake by a sort of telepathy&period; He always floats in with the cup exactly two minutes after I come to life&period; Makes a deuce of a lot of difference to a fellow&rsquor;s day&period;
        p.text &OpenCurlyQuote;How&rsquor;s the weather&comma; Jeeves&quest;&rsquor;
