        p.text
          | I wasn&rsquor;t what you might call in a fever of impatience&period; Bingo little is a chap I was at school with&comma; and we see a lot of each other still&period; He&rsquor;s the nephew of old Mortimer Little&comma; who retired from business recently with a goodish pile&period; &lpar;You&rsquor;ve probably heard of Little&rsquor;s Liniment &ndash; It Limbers Up the Legs&period;&rpar; Bingo biffs about London on a pretty comfortable allowance given him by his uncle&comma; and leads on the whole a fairly unclouded life&period; It wasn&rsquor;t likely that anything which he described as a matter of importance would turn out to be really so frightfully important&period; I took it that he had discovered some new brand of cigarette which he wanted me to try&comma; or something like that&comma; and didn&rsquor;t spoil my breakfast by worrying&period;
        p.text
