        p.text
          | &OpenCurlyQuote;Right ho&excl; Then bring me my whangee&comma; my yellowest gloves&comma; and the old green Homburg&period; I&rsquor;m going into the Park to do pastoral dances&period;&rsquor;
        p.text
          | I don&rsquor;t know if you know that sort of feeling you get on these days round about the end of April and the beginning of May&comma; when the sky&rsquor;s a light blue&comma; with cotton-wool clouds&comma; and there&rsquor;s a bit of a breeze blowing from the west&quest; Kind of uplifted feeling&period; Romantic&comma; if you know what I mean&period; I&rsquor;m not much of a ladies&rsquor; man&comma; but on this particular morning&comma; it seemed to me that what I really wanted was some charming girl to buzz up and ask me to save her from assassins or something&period; So that is was a bit of an anti-climax when I merely ran into young Bingo Little&comma; looking perfectly foul in a crimson satin tie decorated with horseshoes&period;
